# Company: NetFabric

- Website: https://netfabric.ai
- Founder(s): Benjamin Bichsel
- Location: San Francisco, US
- Primary Category: Platform Engineering / Internal Developer Platforms

## What they do
NetFabric provides a platform to automate and standardize cloud infrastructure and internal developer workflows.

## Target user (ICP)
Platform engineers, DevOps teams, mid-to-large engineering organizations.

## Key features
- Infrastructure automation
- Environment standardization
- Platform abstractions
- Developer self-service

## Pricing
Not publicly listed

## Positioning
“Internal platforms without the complexity.”

## Overlap with Clode
- Cloud infrastructure automation
- Platform engineering focus

## How Clode is different
- Clode emphasizes AI-driven automation
- Stronger focus on day-2 operations and monitoring

## DevRel angle
Talk about reducing operational toil beyond platform setup.

## Content hooks
1. Why most internal platforms fail at day-2 operations
2. Platforms should remove work, not add dashboards
